# Spring Modulith Compliance Rules

## Module Boundaries
- Verify module structure follows Spring Modulith conventions
- Ensure only facade classes are publicly accessible
- Validate that internal packages remain encapsulated
- Use ApplicationModuleTest for boundary verification

## Event-Driven Architecture
- Use Spring Application Events for inter-module communication
- Implement proper event publishing and listening
- Include transactional event handling where appropriate
- Document event contracts between modules

## Testing Requirements
- Include @ApplicationModuleTest for each module
- Test module boundaries and encapsulation
- Verify event publishing and handling works correctly
- Include integration tests for facade operations

## JDK 21 Features
- Leverage virtual threads for I/O operations
- Use modern Java features (records, pattern matching, text blocks)
- Apply structured concurrency patterns where beneficial
- Optimize for performance with contemporary JVM features

